# Videos API

A REST API for managing videos, built with Node.js, Fastify, and PostgreSQL.

## 🚀 Technologies

- [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/)
- [Fastify](https://fastify.dev/)
- [PostgreSQL](https://www.postgresql.org/) via [Neon](https://neon.tech/)
- [postgres.js](https://github.com/porsager/postgres)

## ⚙️ Setup

1. Clone the repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/seu-usuario/videos-api
cd videos-api
```

2. Install dependencies
```bash
npm install
```

3. Create a `.env` file in the root directory
```env
DATABASE_URL=your_neon_database_url
```

4. Create the database table
```bash
node create-table.js
```

5. Start the server
```bash
node server.js
```

Server will be running at `http://localhost:3333`

## 📡 Endpoints

| Method | Route | Description |
|--------|-------|-------------|
| GET | `/videos` | List all videos |
| GET | `/videos?search=query` | Search videos by title |
| POST | `/videos` | Create a new video |
| PUT | `/videos/:id` | Update a video |
| DELETE | `/videos/:id` | Delete a video |

## 📝 Request Body (POST/PUT)

```json
{
  "title": "Video title",
  "description": "Video description",
  "duration": 180
}
```